'''The State Commission for Radio Frequencies''' ({{lang-ru|Государственная комиссия по радиочастотам (ГКРЧ)}}) is an inter-agency coordinating body under the [[Ministry of Communications and Mass Media (Russia)|Ministry of Communications and Mass Media of the Russian Federation]], which has full authority in the regulation of [[radio spectrum]]. The commission is organized in accordance with Article 22 of the Federal Communications Law number 126-FZ dated July 7, 2003. The commission carries out on a collective basis to regulate the use of radio spectrum in the Russian Federation.


